        h2 About DressUp!
        p I wrote this app for a friend who wanted to keep track of her clothes from a easy, portable location. For example, when shopping she can use the app to determine what she already owns, what it looks like (via a small picture of the actual object she took with the camera's phone), how much it cost and when and where she bought it from. This way, she can prevent herself from buying something very similar to something she already owns. The app also saves 'outfits' which are combinations of a top, bottom, shoes, accessories, and outerwear so she can see what goes good with what. The app allows her to browse her clothes (or outfits containing certain clothes) by attributes of each type (i.e., search for red tops, shoes that cost less than $20, or all jeans bought before June 2012 with a size of 4 or smaller. The project involved Android development.
        p More details coming soon. <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />
        h2 About AsPlanned!
        p This app is just a simple tool that I designed for exclusive use between me and my friends who enjoy playing billiards together. It keeps track of player's stats, including how many games we've played, who won each game (and by how much, and when each game is played with a graph over time of the wins vs. losses. Really just a fun and easy way to make games more interesting with friends. The name comes from the fact that when we play each game, usually one player will make an absurdely good shot that was unintentional, however we will always say "That shot went as planned!" even though it clearly wasn't. The app counts how many "as-planned" moments occur each game so we can mock whomever relies the most on miraclulous spouts of luck. The project involved Android development.
        p More details coming soon.